The paper deals with extending answer set semantics to deal with inconsistent programs, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of preferred answer sets in repairing databases, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with logic programming (cs.PL), which is a subfield of computer science that deals with the use of logic for programming.
